rComments: tough lecture but easy to get high grade

Course material was comprehensible; professor's explanation using simplified math & geometry was detail to just the right degree. I enjoyed the course very much. That being said. problem sets tend to be easy 2-3 step problems, whereas midterm and final are exclusively cascade-type questions. This prof would've been a solid choice otherwise.
You have to admit that he real puts a lot effort on lecture.

Probably the worst lecturer in the whole faculty; his lectures are overly long and thoroughly unengaging, with little to no class participation allowed. During the 3-hour lectures I took with him, he would often go overtime and give no breaks. Very stubborn. In general, assignments and tests are nigh-incomprehensible. At least he grades generously.
